---
globs: backend/*,frontend/*
alwaysApply: false
---

- Validate and sanitize all inputs on client and server side
- Sanitize HTML content to prevent XSS attacks
- Use Content Security Policy headers
- Implement rate limiting with different limits for different endpoints
- Configure CORS with specific origins (no wildcards in production)
- Log suspicious activity
- Never commit secrets to version control
- Use environment variables for sensitive data
- Validate required environment variables on startup
- Use different secrets for different environments
- Don't expose sensitive information in error messages
- Log security events for monitoring and alerting
- Implement error boundaries for React components
